description: Returns a list of rule groups namespaces in a workspace.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: The token for the next set of items to return. You receive this token from a previous call, and use it to get the next page of results. The other parameters must be the same as the initial call. For example, if your initial request has maxResults of 10, and there are 12 rule groups namespaces to return, then your initial request will return 10 and a nextToken. Using the next token in a subsequent call will return the remaining 2 namespaces.

parameters.name: workspaceId
parameters.description: The ID of the workspace containing the rule groups namespaces.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: A token indicating that there are more results to retrieve. You can use this token as part of your next ListRuleGroupsNamespaces request to retrieve those results.

nested_items.name: ruleGroupsNamespaces
nested_items.description: The returned list of rule groups namespaces.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The ARN of the rule groups namespace.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The date and time that the rule groups namespace was created.

nested_items.name: modifiedAt
nested_items.description: The date and time that the rule groups namespace was most recently changed.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: The name of the rule groups namespace.

nested_items.name: statusCode
nested_items.description: The current status of the namespace.

nested_items.name: statusReason
nested_items.description: The reason for the failure, if any.
